goal:
Through this course, the students will be able to:
- acquire a basic knowledge of social businesses and their challenges;
- understand the nature and causes of emerging social businesses in Japan;
- analyse the potential and limitations of business activities to address various social issues; and
- improve oral and written communication skills through discussions and writing essays.

notes_url:
For easily accessible and accurate information on current topics and trends in Japanese law in English (with comparative perspectives), see: Waseda Bulletin of Comparative Law (
https://www.waseda.jp/folaw/icl/en/public/bulletin/
)
